MEME motif group analysis¶

Cleaned document to display the gene list and expression parallel coordinates plot for exploring groups of genes which may have regulatory similarities.

Motif groups displayed below:

  1. Top expression, Low CV, TAVTAT motif from DREME
  2. Top expression, Low CV, TAVTAT motif from DREME
  3. Top expression, Low CV, TTRTAAG motif from DREME
  4. Top expression, Low CV, all genes
  1. All loci through MEME, Motif-1
  2. All loci through MEME, Motif-2
  3. All loci through MEME, Motif-9
  4. All loci through MEME, Motif-27

mdf = pd.read_csv("data/mean_df_for_parCoords.tsv",sep='\t').fillna("")

# impose a specific x-axis sort order on the df
list_ordering = ['uMax','lowCH4','NoCu','lowCu','medCu','highCu','NO3_lowO2_slow_growth','highO2_slow_growth','lowO2_fast_growth','MeOH','NoLanthanum','WithLanthanum'] 
mdf["exp_condition_order"] = pd.Categorical(mdf["exp_condition"], categories=list_ordering)

Load groups of genes with motif of interest¶

In [3]:
def load_top_genes_from_file(filename):
    '''
    Load list of gene names from top saved file
    '''
    with open(filename, 'r') as f:
        genes = [x.strip() for x in f.readlines()]
    
    return genes

# motifs found via DREME in low CV top group
meme_tavtat = load_top_genes_from_file(f'data/top_genes_nk/TAVTAT_genes.tsv')
meme_tavtat_mdf = mdf[mdf['locus_tag'].isin(meme_tavtat)]

meme_tagaak = load_top_genes_from_file(f'data/top_genes_nk/TAGAAK_lowCV_genes.tsv')
meme_tagaak_mdf = mdf[mdf['locus_tag'].isin(meme_tagaak)]

meme_ttr = load_top_genes_from_file(f'data/top_genes_nk/TTRTAAG_lowCV_genes.tsv')
meme_ttr_mdf = mdf[mdf['locus_tag'].isin(meme_ttr)]

low_cv_gene = load_top_genes_from_file(f'data/top_genes_nk/low_cv_topn4k2_genes.tsv')
low_cv_gene_mdf = mdf[mdf['locus_tag'].isin(low_cv_gene)]


# motifs found via MEME from all loci
meme1 = load_top_genes_from_file(f'../meme_tinker/all_loci_motif_groups/meme1.txt')
meme1_mdf = mdf[mdf['locus_tag'].isin(meme1)]

meme2 = load_top_genes_from_file(f'../meme_tinker/all_loci_motif_groups/meme2.txt')
meme2_mdf = mdf[mdf['locus_tag'].isin(meme2)]

meme9 = load_top_genes_from_file(f'../meme_tinker/all_loci_motif_groups/meme9.txt')
meme9_mdf = mdf[mdf['locus_tag'].isin(meme9)]

meme27 = load_top_genes_from_file(f'../meme_tinker/all_loci_motif_groups/meme27.txt')
meme27_mdf = mdf[mdf['locus_tag'].isin(meme27)]
In [4]:
def view_df(df):
    print(f"Gene count: {len(df['locus_tag'].unique())}")
    return df[['mage_id','mage_gene','locus_tag','gene_symbol','product']].drop_duplicates().sort_values('locus_tag').reset_index()

Explore parallel coordinates plots and gene lists¶

To interact with the plot:

  • scroll with the mouse wheel to zoom
  • click and drag to pan up and down
  • select genes to highlight in the legend
  • hold shift to select multiple genes in the legend
  • click legend whitespace to clear selection
